## 2. Key XML Schemas

### MerchantPricing.xsd
**Purpose:** Core merchant pricing profile structure

**Key Types:**
```xml
<MerchantPricingRequestType>
  <Merchant> - Identification (BankNum, MerchantNum)
  <Agent> - Optional RP agent (6-digit code)
  <ErgId> - Optional expense rate group link
  <MinimumDiscount> - Minimum monthly charge configuration
  <Fees> - Collection of fee items
</MerchantPricingRequestType>
```

**MinimumDiscount Structure:**
- **Amount** - Minimum charge amount
- **StartDate** / **StopDate** - Effective date range
- **BillingMethod** - D (Deduct) or R (Reverse)
- **Frequency** - Monthly flags (Jan-Dec)
- **RateRestriction** - Rate locks and ranges
- **GLItemCode** / **UserDataCode** - Accounting codes

**Boarding Status Codes:**
- P - Pending
- B - Boarded
- D - Deactivated
- C - Closed

### ProfilePricing.xsd
**Purpose:** Fee item structures and pricing configurations

**Fee Categories (1-15):**
1. Authorization Transactions
2. Authorization Other
3. Data Capture Transactions
4. Data Capture Other
5. Exceptions
6. Debit Network
7. EBT (Electronic Benefits Transfer)
8. MISC Per Item Fees
9. MISC Fixed Fees
10. Interchange
11. Individual Plan
12. Discount
13. Card Brand Fees
15. Transaction Method

**FeeRequestType Structure:**
```xml
<Fee>
  <FeeIdentity>
    <Category> - Fee category (1-15)
    <Name> - Fee name (30 chars max)
    <ModifiedName> - Optional alternate name
  </FeeIdentity>
  <TemplateIdentity> - Optional template reference
  <KeyStructure> - 1-4 key values defining fee applicability
  <DdaAccountOverride> - Optional account override
  <Frequency> - Monthly application flags
  <Setting> - Tax, billing, GL/User codes
  <StatementSetting> - Display preferences
  <Pricing> - Rate configuration
  <RateRestriction> - Rate locks/ranges
</Fee>
```

**Pricing Methods:**
- **Per Item** - Fixed amount per transaction
- **Percentage** - Percentage of transaction amount
- **Volume Tiered** - Different rates based on volume thresholds
  - Pick-a-Tier (P) - Single tier applies
  - Fill-a-Tier (F) - Progressive tiers
- **Pass-Through** - Interchange pass-through + markup
- **Differential** - Interchange differential pricing

**Tier Configuration:**
```xml
<VolumeTier>
  <TierType>V</TierType> <!-- Volume -->
  <VolumeTierMethod>P or F</VolumeTierMethod>
  <VolumeTierBasedOn>
    A - Amount
    N - Number of transactions
    V - Average ticket
    P - Percentage of total
  </VolumeTierBasedOn>
  <Rates>
    <DateRate>
      <StartDate>
      <StopDate>
      <Tiers>
        <Tier>
          <MinFactor> - Threshold amount/count
          <Amount> - Per-item rate
          <Percent> - Percentage rate
        </Tier>
      </Tiers>
    </DateRate>
  </Rates>
</VolumeTier>
```

**Effective Rate Scheduling:**
Multiple DateRate elements allow scheduling future rate changes:
```xml
<Pricing>
  <DateRate>
    <StartDate>06/01/2015</StartDate>
    <StopDate>06/30/2015</StopDate>
    <Percent>1.00</Percent>
  </DateRate>
  <DateRate>
    <StartDate>07/01/2015</StartDate>
    <StopDate>07/31/2015</StopDate>
    <Percent>1.20</Percent>
  </DateRate>
</Pricing>
```

### ERG.xsd (Expense Rate Groups)
**Purpose:** Expense tracking and cost allocation

**ERG Hierarchy Levels:**
- **Client Level** - Applies across all banks
- **Bank Level** - Specific bank(s)
- **Group Level** - Bank + Group
- **Association Level** - Bank + Association

**ERG Structure:**
```xml
<ErgType>
  <ErgId> - Unique identifier
  <ErgHierarchy>
    <ClientLevel|BankLevel|GroupLevel|AssociationLevel>
      <BankNum> - 4 digits
      <GroupNum> - 6 digits (if applicable)
      <AssociationNum> - 6 digits (if applicable)
    </>
  </ErgHierarchy>
  <UserRestriction> - Y/N for user access control
  <ErgStatus> - Active/Inactive
  <ExpenseFees> - Collection of expense items (up to 100)
</ErgType>
```

**RP ERG (Relationship Profitability):**
Specialized ERGs for agent commission structures:
```xml
<RpErgType>
  <RpErgId>
  <RpErgHierarchy>
    <BankLevel|AgentLevel> - Two-level hierarchy
  </RpErgHierarchy>
  <RpErgType> - Commission/payout type
  <ExpenseFees> - Agent expense/payout fees
</RpErgType>
```

### MerchantDDA.xsd (Bank Account Management)
**Purpose:** Merchant settlement account configuration

**DDA Account Types:**
- **P** - Primary Account (main settlement)
- **D** - Daily Activity Account
- **C** - Chargeback Account
- **A** - Adjustment Account
- **B** - Debit Activity Account

**Account Structure:**
```xml
<MerchantDDAType>
  <Merchant>
    <BankNum> - 4 digits
    <MerchantNum> - 2-16 digits
  </Merchant>
  <DdaAccount> - Up to 5 accounts
    <TranType> - P/D/C/A/B
    <AccountType> - C (Checking), S (Savings), G (GL)
    <DdaNumber> - 1-17 characters
    <TransitRouting> - 9-digit ABA routing number
  </DdaAccount>
</MerchantDDAType>
```

### PricingCommon.xsd
**Purpose:** Shared data types and common structures

**Key Type Definitions:**

**Frequency Type:**
```xml
<FrequencyType>
  <Jan>Y|N</Jan>
  <Feb>Y|N</Feb>
  <!-- ... through Dec -->
</FrequencyType>
```

**Rate Restriction:**
```xml
<RateRestrictionType>
  <RateLock>Y|N</RateLock> - Prevent rate changes
  <RateRange>
    <Amount>
      <Min>
      <Max>
    </Amount>
    <Percent>
      <Min>
      <Max>
    </Percent>
    <RangeLock>Y|N</RangeLock>
  </RateRange>
</RateRestrictionType>
```

**Key Structure:**
Defines what transactions a fee applies to (1-4 keys per fee):
```xml
<KeyStructureType>
  <Key>Value1</Key>
  <Key>Value2</Key>
  <Key>Value3</Key>
  <Key>Value4</Key>
</KeyStructureType>
```

Valid key structures are maintained in the **PPM Key Structure File** (updated periodically).

### Common.xsd
**Purpose:** Base entity types

**Hierarchy Identifiers:**
```xml
<BankNumType> - 4 digits (e.g., 1234)
<GroupNumType> - 6 digits (e.g., 123456)
<AssocNumType> - 6 digits
<MerchantNumType> - 2-16 digits
<AgentNumType> - 6 digits
```

**Hierarchy Levels:**
- 220 - Client
- 200 - Bank
- 195 - Agent
- 190 - Group
- 180 - Association
- 100 - Merchant

## 3. Pricing Configuration Workflow

### Step 1: Merchant Must Exist in Express
**Prerequisites:**
- Merchant boarded in TSYS Express system
- Bank Number assigned
- Merchant Number generated
- Merchant status = Boarded (B)

**Critical:** PPM will **reject** any SaveMerchantPricing request if the merchant does not exist in the billing system.

### Step 2: Create Merchant Pricing Profile

**Operation:** SaveMerchantPricing

**Process Flow:**
```
1. Submit MerchantPricingRequest
   > Validates merchant exists in system
   > Validates profile data
   > Creates/overwrites profile
   > Returns profile status

2. If fees included:
   > Validates each fee item
   > Checks key structure validity
   > Verifies fee category rules
   > Ensures limits not exceeded (80 direct + 80 inherited per hierarchy level)
   > Returns fee-level outcomes

3. Response:
   > Overall Status (success/failure)
   > ProfileStatus (boarding status)
   > Per-fee Outcome tags
   > Mirror of submitted data with status indicators
```

**Profile Limits:**
- 80 fee items directly on merchant profile
- 80 additional fee items can be inherited from each hierarchy level (bank/group/association)
- Total potential: 320 fee items per merchant
- ERGs: Up to 100 fee items
- Key structures: Up to 4,000 per profile/ERG

### Step 3: Configure Fee Items

**Fee Creation Methods:**

**A. SaveMerchantPricing (Full Profile)**
- Creates new profile or completely replaces existing
- Removes all existing fees and replaces with new set
- Use for: Initial setup, complete pricing overhaul

**B. AddMerchantFees (Incremental)**
- Adds new fees without affecting existing
- Use for: Adding new fee categories, expanding pricing

**C. ModifyMerchantFees (Targeted Updates)**
- Updates specific fees by FeeIdentity
- Existing fees not mentioned remain unchanged
- **Important:** Matching StartDate required to update specific effective rate
- Non-matching future StartDate erases subsequent effective rates
- Use for: Rate adjustments, date changes

**D. ApplyTemplatesToMerchant**
- Applies pre-configured pricing templates
- Templates can be at Client/Bank/Group/Association levels
- Use for: Standardized pricing deployment

### Step 4: Configure DDA Accounts

**Operation:** SaveMerchantDDA

```xml
<MerchantDDARequest>
  <Merchant>
    <BankNum>1234</BankNum>
    <MerchantNum>123456789</MerchantNum>
  </Merchant>
  <DdaAccount>
    <TranType>P</TranType> <!-- Primary -->
    <AccountType>C</AccountType> <!-- Checking -->
    <DdaNumber>123456789</DdaNumber>
    <TransitRouting>121000248</TransitRouting>
  </DdaAccount>
  <DdaAccount>
    <TranType>C</TranType> <!-- Chargebacks -->
    <AccountType>C</AccountType>
    <DdaNumber>987654321</DdaNumber>
    <TransitRouting>121000248</TransitRouting>
  </DdaAccount>
</MerchantDDARequest>
```

### Step 5: Optional ERG Assignment

**If tracking expenses:**
1. Create ERG: AddErg operation
2. Add expense fees: AddErgFees
3. Link to merchant: SaveMerchantPricing with ErgId element

### Step 6: Validation & Activation

**GetMerchantPricing operation:**
- Retrieves complete profile
- Returns all active fees (current + future)
- Returns current month expired fees
- Does NOT return expired fees from previous months
- Includes hierarchical fee items
- Does NOT include ERG expenses (use GetErg separately)

**Fee Status Indicators:**
- **Complete** (C) - Fee fully configured and active
- **Work In Progress** (WIP) - Fee partially configured (GUI only)
- XML-submitted fees always saved as Complete

## 5. Integration Patterns and Best Practices

### A. Express to PPM Integration Pattern

**Step-by-Step Integration:**

```typescript
// 1. Create Express Account
const expressResponse = await createExpressAccount({
  merchantName: mpaData.businessLegalName,
  dbaName: mpaData.dbaName,
  taxId: mpaData.taxId,
  mcc: mpaData.industryMCC,
  // ... other Express fields
});

// 2. Extract Express Identifiers
const { bankNumber, merchantNumber } = expressResponse;

// 3. Wait for Boarding Confirmation
await waitForBoardingStatus(bankNumber, merchantNumber, 'B');

// 4. Configure PPM Pricing
const ppmResponse = await saveMerchantPricing({
  merchant: {
    bankNum: bankNumber,
    merchantNum: merchantNumber
  },
  fees: transformMPAFeesToPPM(mpaData.pricingStructure)
});

// 5. Configure DDA
await saveMerchantDDA({
  merchant: { bankNum: bankNumber, merchantNum: merchantNumber },
  accounts: transformBankAccounts(mpaData.bankingDetails)
});

// 6. Validate Setup
const validation = await getMerchantPricing(bankNumber, merchantNumber);
```

### B. Error Handling Patterns

**Response Validation:**
```typescript
interface PPMResponse {
  responseMetaData: {
    code: number;
    description: string;
  };
  merchantPricing: {
    profileStatus: {
      code: number;
      description: string;
    };
    fees: Array<{
      outcome: {
        code: number;
        description: string;
      };
    }>;
  };
}

// Check overall response
if (response.responseMetaData.code !== 0) {
  throw new PPMError(response.responseMetaData.description);
}

// Check profile status
if (response.merchantPricing.profileStatus.code !== 0) {
  throw new ProfileError(response.merchantPricing.profileStatus.description);
}

// Check individual fee outcomes
const failedFees = response.merchantPricing.fees
  .filter(fee => fee.outcome.code !== 0);

if (failedFees.length > 0) {
  // Handle partial success
  logFailedFees(failedFees);
}
```

**Common Error Codes:**
- Code 0 - Success
- Merchant not found - Merchant doesn't exist in billing system
- Invalid key structure - Key combination not in PPM Key Structure File
- Fee limit exceeded - More than 80 direct fees on profile
- Invalid fee category - Business rule violation for fee category
- Duplicate fee - Fee with same identity already exists
- Invalid date range - StartDate after StopDate or expired dates

### D. Rate Update Patterns

**Modifying Existing Rates:**
```typescript
// Safe rate update - matches existing start date
async function updateExistingRate(
  bankNum: string,
  merchantNum: string,
  feeName: string,
  newRate: number
) {
  // 1. Get current pricing
  const current = await getMerchantPricing(bankNum, merchantNum);
  
  // 2. Find fee to update
  const fee = current.fees.find(f => f.feeIdentity.name === feeName);
  if (!fee) throw new Error('Fee not found');
  
  // 3. Get current effective rate
  const currentRate = fee.pricing.percentWithPerItem.dateRate;
  
  // 4. Modify with SAME start date to update in place
  await modifyMerchantFees({
    merchant: { bankNum, merchantNum },
    fees: [{
      feeIdentity: fee.feeIdentity,
      pricing: {
        percentWithPerItem: {
          dateRate: {
            startDate: currentRate.startDate, // MUST MATCH
            stopDate: currentRate.stopDate,
            percent: newRate,
            amount: currentRate.amount,
            countChargeType: currentRate.countChargeType,
            amountChargeType: currentRate.amountChargeType
          }
        }
      }
    }]
  });
}

// Schedule future rate change
async function scheduleFutureRate(
  bankNum: string,
  merchantNum: string,
  feeName: string,
  effectiveDate: Date,
  newRate: number
) {
  const current = await getMerchantPricing(bankNum, merchantNum);
  const fee = current.fees.find(f => f.feeIdentity.name === feeName);
  
  // Add new effective rate
  await modifyMerchantFees({
    merchant: { bankNum, merchantNum },
    fees: [{
      feeIdentity: fee.feeIdentity,
      pricing: {
        percentWithPerItem: {
          dateRate: {
            startDate: formatDate(effectiveDate), // NEW DATE
            stopDate: '12/31/9999',
            percent: newRate,
            // ... other fields
          }
        }
      }
    }]
  });
}
```

```typescript
// Generate batch request file

// Upload to mailbox
async function submitBatch(
  batchXML: string,
  clientShortName: string,
  batchId: string
): Promise<string> {
  const filename = `${clientShortName}_MerchantPricingReq_${batchId}.xml`;
  
  await uploadToMailbox(filename, batchXML);
  
  return filename;
}

// Poll for response
async function waitForBatchResponse(
  requestFilename: string
): Promise<BatchResponse> {
  const responseFilename = requestFilename.replace('Req', 'Res');
  
  let attempts = 0;
  while (attempts < 30) { // 30 attempts = ~15 minutes
    const response = await checkMailbox(responseFilename);
    if (response) {
      return parseBatchResponse(response);
    }
    await sleep(30000); // Wait 30 seconds
    attempts++;
  }
  
  throw new Error('Batch response timeout');
}
```

### F. Key Structure Management

**Key Structure Validation:**
```typescript
// Load and cache valid key structures
class KeyStructureValidator {
  private validKeys: Map<number, Set<string[]>>;
  
  async loadKeyStructures() {
    // Load from PPM Key Structure File
    const keyFile = await fetchPPMKeyStructureFile();
    this.validKeys = parseKeyStructureFile(keyFile);
  }
  
  validateKeyStructure(
    category: number,
    keys: string[]
  ): boolean {
    const validKeysForCategory = this.validKeys.get(category);
    if (!validKeysForCategory) return false;
    
    return validKeysForCategory.has(keys.join('|'));
  }
  
  suggestValidKeys(category: number): string[][] {
    return Array.from(this.validKeys.get(category) || [])
      .map(k => k.split('|'));
  }
}
```

## 7. Relationship Between PPM and Express

### Integration Architecture

```

                     TSYS Ecosystem                           

                                                               
                    
    TSYS Express                    PPM                 
    (Merchant                   (Pricing &              
     Boarding)                   Billing)               
                    
                                                           
            Creates                     Configures         
             Bank Number                Fee Items        
             Merchant Number            Rate Schedules   
             Account Status             DDA Accounts     
                                         ERGs             
                                                           
                               
                                                            
                  Merchant ID                                
                  (BankNum + MerchantNum)                   
                                                            
                                  
             Billing/Statement                            
                 System                                   
                                  
                                                              

```

### Key Relationships

**1. Merchant Identity:**
- Express creates the merchant record and assigns BankNum + MerchantNum
- PPM references merchants by BankNum + MerchantNum
- **PPM cannot create merchants** - they must exist in Express first

**2. Data Dependencies:**

| Express Data | PPM Requirement | Notes |
|--------------|-----------------|-------|
| Merchant Number | Required | Primary identifier for PPM operations |
| Bank Number | Required | Hierarchy level identifier |
| Boarding Status | Must be "B" (Boarded) | PPM rejects if merchant not boarded |
| DBA Name | Optional reference | For PPM reporting |
| MCC | Optional reference | Can influence fee categories |

**3. Operational Sequence:**

```
Step 1: Express - Create Merchant Account
    Returns: BankNum, MerchantNum
   
Step 2: Express - Complete Boarding Process
    Status changes to "B" (Boarded)
   
Step 3: PPM - SaveMerchantPricing (NOW ALLOWED)
    Creates pricing profile
   
Step 4: PPM - SaveMerchantDDA
    Configures settlement accounts
   
Step 5: Billing System - Generates Statements
    Uses PPM pricing + Express merchant data
```

**4. Shared Data Elements:**

**Merchant Identification (Both Systems):**
- BankNum (4 digits)
- MerchantNum (2-16 digits)

**Express-Only Data:**
- Legal Name, DBA
- Tax ID
- Business Address
- Owner Information
- MCC
- Processing Limits

**PPM-Only Data:**
- Fee Items
- Pricing Rates
- ERG Assignments
- Agent Assignments (for RP)
- Minimum Discount
- Rate Restrictions

**Shared/Referenced:**
- DDA Account Numbers (Express creates, PPM references)
- Bank routing numbers
- Merchant status

**5. Error Handling:**

If PPM receives a request for non-existent merchant:
```xml
<Response>
  <ResponseMetaData>
    <Code>ERROR_CODE</Code>
    <Description>Merchant not found in billing system</Description>
  </ResponseMetaData>
</Response>
```

Resolution: Ensure merchant exists in Express and is boarded before calling PPM.

### B. Data Validation Strategy

**1. Pre-submission Validation:**
```typescript
interface ValidationRule {
  field: string;
  validate: (value: any) => boolean;
  message: string;
}

const merchantPricingRules: ValidationRule[] = [
  {
    field: 'merchant.bankNum',
    validate: (v) => /^\d{4}$/.test(v),
    message: 'Bank number must be 4 digits'
  },
  {
    field: 'merchant.merchantNum',
    validate: (v) => /^\d{2,16}$/.test(v),
    message: 'Merchant number must be 2-16 digits'
  },
  // ... more rules
];

function validatePPMRequest(request: any): ValidationResult {
  const errors: string[] = [];
  
  for (const rule of merchantPricingRules) {
    const value = getNestedValue(request, rule.field);
    if (!rule.validate(value)) {
      errors.push(rule.message);
    }
  }
  
  return { valid: errors.length === 0, errors };
}
```

**2. Key Structure Validation:**
```typescript
// Load valid key structures on startup
const keyStructureCache = new Map<number, Set<string>>();

async function loadKeyStructures() {
  // Fetch from PPM Key Structure File or cached version
  const structures = await fetchPPMKeyStructures();
  
  for (const [category, keys] of structures) {
    keyStructureCache.set(
      category,
      new Set(keys.map(k => k.join('|')))
    );
  }
}

function validateKeyStructure(
  category: number,
  keys: string[]
): boolean {
  const validKeys = keyStructureCache.get(category);
  if (!validKeys) return false;
  
  return validKeys.has(keys.join('|'));
}
```

### D. Monitoring and Logging

**1. Comprehensive Logging:**
```typescript
interface PPMOperationLog {
  operation: string;
  timestamp: Date;
  bankNum: string;
  merchantNum: string;
  requestSize: number;
  responseCode: number;
  responseTime: number;
  errors?: string[];
}

async function loggedPPMOperation<T>(
  operation: string,
  request: any,
  execute: () => Promise<T>
): Promise<T> {
  const startTime = Date.now();
  const log: PPMOperationLog = {
    operation,
    timestamp: new Date(),
    bankNum: request.merchant?.bankNum,
    merchantNum: request.merchant?.merchantNum,
    requestSize: JSON.stringify(request).length,
    responseCode: 0,
    responseTime: 0
  };
  
  try {
    const result = await execute();
    log.responseCode = result.responseMetaData?.code || 0;
    log.responseTime = Date.now() - startTime;
    
    // Log to database/monitoring system
    await saveOperationLog(log);
    
    return result;
  } catch (error) {
    log.responseCode = -1;
    log.responseTime = Date.now() - startTime;
    log.errors = [error.message];
    
    await saveOperationLog(log);
    throw error;
  }
}
```

## Summary of Critical Integration Points

### 1. **Prerequisites**
- Merchant must exist in TSYS Express
- Merchant must be boarded (status = "B")
- BankNum and MerchantNum must be obtained from Express

### 2. **Primary Operations**
- **SaveMerchantPricing** - Initial pricing setup after Express boarding
- **AddMerchantFees** - Incremental fee additions
- **ModifyMerchantFees** - Rate updates (careful with date matching)
- **GetMerchantPricing** - Validation and retrieval
- **SaveMerchantDDA** - Bank account configuration

### 3. **Data Transformation Requirements**
- MPA discount rates  PPM Discount fees (Category 12)
- MPA monthly fees  PPM MISC Fixed fees (Category 9)
- MPA transaction fees  PPM Auth/Data Capture fees (Categories 1, 3)
- MPA bank account  PPM DDA configuration

### 4. **Critical Business Rules**
- Fee items limited to 80 direct + 80 per hierarchy level
- Key structures must be in valid combinations
- Date ranges: StartDate cannot be in past for new fees
- Effective rates require StopDate on all but final rate
- XML-submitted fees always saved as Complete status

### 5. **Error Handling**
- Check ResponseMetaData.Code (0 = success)
- Check ProfileStatus.Code for profile-level errors
- Check individual Fee.Outcome.Code for fee-level errors
- Log all failed operations for audit trail

# TSYS Portfolio Pricing Manager (PPM) XML SDK - Comprehensive Analysis Report

## Executive Summary

TSYS Portfolio Pricing Manager (PPM) is a pricing and billing management system that enables clients to configure merchant pricing, track expenses, and manage fee structures for their merchant portfolios. The system integrates with TSYS Express (merchant account creation) and operates through both a web-based GUI and XML API interfaces.

**Critical Integration Flow:**
```
Express Account Creation  PPM Pricing Configuration  Statement/Billing Integration
```

The merchant must exist in TSYS's boarding system (via Express) **before** PPM pricing can be configured.

## 1. Main API Operations: Batch vs Real-Time

### Real-Time Operations (WSDL-based)

**Location:** `/Users/coreyyoung/Desktop/Projects/tsyscrm/TSYS-DOCS/PPM-XML-WSDLSchemas-RealTime/MerchantPricingService.wsdl`

PPM provides a comprehensive SOAP-based web service with the following operation categories:

#### Merchant Pricing Operations
- **SaveMerchantPricing** - Creates new or overwrites existing merchant pricing profile
- **GetMerchantPricing** - Retrieves merchant pricing profile and all associated fees
- **DeleteMerchantPricing** - Removes merchant pricing profile entirely
- **AddMerchantFees** - Adds new fees to existing profile without affecting others
- **ModifyMerchantFees** - Updates specific existing fees
- **AddOrModifyMerchantFees** - Combined operation for adding or modifying fees
- **DeleteMerchantFees** - Removes specific fees from profile
- **ModifyMerchantFeesFrequencyAndRates** - Updates only frequency and rate information
- **ApplyTemplatesToMerchant** - Applies pre-configured pricing templates
- **ReassignTemplateToMerchant** - Changes template assignment

#### Hierarchy Pricing Operations
- **SaveHierarchyPricing** - Creates/updates pricing at bank, group, or association level
- **GetHierarchyPricing** - Retrieves hierarchical pricing structures
- **DeleteHierarchyPricing** - Removes hierarchical pricing
- **AddHierarchyFees** - Adds fees to hierarchy level
- **ModifyHierarchyFees** - Updates hierarchy fees

#### ERG (Expense Rate Group) Operations
- **AddErg** - Creates new expense rate group
- **ModifyErg** - Updates ERG configuration
- **DeleteErg** - Removes ERG
- **GetErg** - Retrieves ERG details
- **AddErgFees** - Adds expense fees to ERG
- **ModifyErgFees** - Updates ERG fees
- **DeleteErgFees** - Removes ERG fees

#### RP (Relationship Profitability) Operations
- **AddRpErg** - Creates RP expense rate group for agent commissions
- **ModifyRpErg** - Updates RP ERG
- **DeleteRpErg** - Removes RP ERG
- **GetRpErg** - Retrieves RP ERG details
- **AddRpErgFees** - Adds RP fees
- **ModifyRpErgFees** - Updates RP fees
- **DeleteRpErgFees** - Removes RP fees
- **AddRpAgent** - Creates agent profile
- **ModifyRpAgent** - Updates agent
- **DeleteRpAgent** - Removes agent
- **GetRpAgent** - Retrieves agent details

#### DDA (Direct Deposit Account) Operations
- **SaveMerchantDDA** - Configures merchant bank account information
- **GetMerchantDDA** - Retrieves DDA details
- **DeleteMerchantDDA** - Removes DDA configuration

#### Fee Item Master Operations (2023+ Features)
- **GetFeeItemMaster** - Retrieves fee item master data
- **GetFeeItemMasterFeeDetails** - Detailed fee item information
- **AddFeeItemMasterFees** - Adds fees to master catalog
- **ModifyFeeItemMasterFees** - Updates fee items in catalog
- **ModifyFeeItemMasterFeesMinimal** - Limited update operation

#### Income Rate Group Operations (2023+)
- **AssignIrgsToMerchant** - Assigns Income Rate Groups to merchant
- **UnAssignIrgsFromMerchant** - Removes IRG assignments

### Batch Operations (File-based)

**Schemas:** 
- `/Users/coreyyoung/Desktop/Projects/tsyscrm/TSYS-DOCS/PPM-XML-Schemas-Batch/BatchRequestMBE.xsd`
- `/Users/coreyyoung/Desktop/Projects/tsyscrm/TSYS-DOCS/PPM-XML-Schemas-Batch/BatchResponseMBE.xsd`

#### Batch Processing Characteristics

**Delivery Method:**
- Files uploaded to client-specific mailbox
- Processed multiple times per day (schedule TBD during implementation)
- Response files returned to same mailbox

**File Naming Convention:**
```
ClientShortName_RequestGroupType_BatchID_XXXX.xml
```

**Request Group Types:**
- `MerchantPricingReq` / `MerchantPricingRes`
- `HierarchyPricingReq` / `HierarchyPricingRes`
- `ErgReq` / `ErgRes`
- `RpErgReq` / `RpErgRes`
- `RpAgentReq` / `RpAgentRes`
- `MerchantDDAReq` / `MerchantDDARes`

**Batch Rules:**
- Requests of the same entity type can be combined (e.g., SaveMerchantPricing + ModifyMerchantFees)
- Cannot mix entity types (e.g., merchant pricing + hierarchy pricing in same file)
- Must maintain logical order (Get before Delete, Save before Modify)
- No file size or transaction limits
- Unlimited daily batch submissions

**Example Filenames:**
```
FirstLocalBank_MerchantPricingReq_1234567.xml
BankOfMine_RpAgentReq_08012013_AddingSWOffice.xml
SecondRegionalBank_HierarchyPricingReq_82821_NewAssociation.xml
```

## 2. Key XML Schemas

### MerchantPricing.xsd
**Purpose:** Core merchant pricing profile structure

**Key Types:**
```xml
<MerchantPricingRequestType>
  <Merchant> - Identification (BankNum, MerchantNum)
  <Agent> - Optional RP agent (6-digit code)
  <ErgId> - Optional expense rate group link
  <MinimumDiscount> - Minimum monthly charge configuration
  <Fees> - Collection of fee items
</MerchantPricingRequestType>
```

**MinimumDiscount Structure:**
- **Amount** - Minimum charge amount
- **StartDate** / **StopDate** - Effective date range
- **BillingMethod** - D (Deduct) or R (Reverse)
- **Frequency** - Monthly flags (Jan-Dec)
- **RateRestriction** - Rate locks and ranges
- **GLItemCode** / **UserDataCode** - Accounting codes

**Boarding Status Codes:**
- P - Pending
- B - Boarded
- D - Deactivated
- C - Closed

### ProfilePricing.xsd
**Purpose:** Fee item structures and pricing configurations

**Fee Categories (1-15):**
1. Authorization Transactions
2. Authorization Other
3. Data Capture Transactions
4. Data Capture Other
5. Exceptions
6. Debit Network
7. EBT (Electronic Benefits Transfer)
8. MISC Per Item Fees
9. MISC Fixed Fees
10. Interchange
11. Individual Plan
12. Discount
13. Card Brand Fees
15. Transaction Method

**FeeRequestType Structure:**
```xml
<Fee>
  <FeeIdentity>
    <Category> - Fee category (1-15)
    <Name> - Fee name (30 chars max)
    <ModifiedName> - Optional alternate name
  </FeeIdentity>
  <TemplateIdentity> - Optional template reference
  <KeyStructure> - 1-4 key values defining fee applicability
  <DdaAccountOverride> - Optional account override
  <Frequency> - Monthly application flags
  <Setting> - Tax, billing, GL/User codes
  <StatementSetting> - Display preferences
  <Pricing> - Rate configuration
  <RateRestriction> - Rate locks/ranges
</Fee>
```

**Pricing Methods:**
- **Per Item** - Fixed amount per transaction
- **Percentage** - Percentage of transaction amount
- **Volume Tiered** - Different rates based on volume thresholds
  - Pick-a-Tier (P) - Single tier applies
  - Fill-a-Tier (F) - Progressive tiers
- **Pass-Through** - Interchange pass-through + markup
- **Differential** - Interchange differential pricing

**Tier Configuration:**
```xml
<VolumeTier>
  <TierType>V</TierType> <!-- Volume -->
  <VolumeTierMethod>P or F</VolumeTierMethod>
  <VolumeTierBasedOn>
    A - Amount
    N - Number of transactions
    V - Average ticket
    P - Percentage of total
  </VolumeTierBasedOn>
  <Rates>
    <DateRate>
      <StartDate>
      <StopDate>
      <Tiers>
        <Tier>
          <MinFactor> - Threshold amount/count
          <Amount> - Per-item rate
          <Percent> - Percentage rate
        </Tier>
      </Tiers>
    </DateRate>
  </Rates>
</VolumeTier>
```

**Effective Rate Scheduling:**
Multiple DateRate elements allow scheduling future rate changes:
```xml
<Pricing>
  <DateRate>
    <StartDate>06/01/2015</StartDate>
    <StopDate>06/30/2015</StopDate>
    <Percent>1.00</Percent>
  </DateRate>
  <DateRate>
    <StartDate>07/01/2015</StartDate>
    <StopDate>07/31/2015</StopDate>
    <Percent>1.20</Percent>
  </DateRate>
</Pricing>
```

### ERG.xsd (Expense Rate Groups)
**Purpose:** Expense tracking and cost allocation

**ERG Hierarchy Levels:**
- **Client Level** - Applies across all banks
- **Bank Level** - Specific bank(s)
- **Group Level** - Bank + Group
- **Association Level** - Bank + Association

**ERG Structure:**
```xml
<ErgType>
  <ErgId> - Unique identifier
  <ErgHierarchy>
    <ClientLevel|BankLevel|GroupLevel|AssociationLevel>
      <BankNum> - 4 digits
      <GroupNum> - 6 digits (if applicable)
      <AssociationNum> - 6 digits (if applicable)
    </>
  </ErgHierarchy>
  <UserRestriction> - Y/N for user access control
  <ErgStatus> - Active/Inactive
  <ExpenseFees> - Collection of expense items (up to 100)
</ErgType>
```

**RP ERG (Relationship Profitability):**
Specialized ERGs for agent commission structures:
```xml
<RpErgType>
  <RpErgId>
  <RpErgHierarchy>
    <BankLevel|AgentLevel> - Two-level hierarchy
  </RpErgHierarchy>
  <RpErgType> - Commission/payout type
  <ExpenseFees> - Agent expense/payout fees
</RpErgType>
```

### MerchantDDA.xsd (Bank Account Management)
**Purpose:** Merchant settlement account configuration

**DDA Account Types:**
- **P** - Primary Account (main settlement)
- **D** - Daily Activity Account
- **C** - Chargeback Account
- **A** - Adjustment Account
- **B** - Debit Activity Account

**Account Structure:**
```xml
<MerchantDDAType>
  <Merchant>
    <BankNum> - 4 digits
    <MerchantNum> - 2-16 digits
  </Merchant>
  <DdaAccount> - Up to 5 accounts
    <TranType> - P/D/C/A/B
    <AccountType> - C (Checking), S (Savings), G (GL)
    <DdaNumber> - 1-17 characters
    <TransitRouting> - 9-digit ABA routing number
  </DdaAccount>
</MerchantDDAType>
```

### PricingCommon.xsd
**Purpose:** Shared data types and common structures

**Key Type Definitions:**

**Frequency Type:**
```xml
<FrequencyType>
  <Jan>Y|N</Jan>
  <Feb>Y|N</Feb>
  <!-- ... through Dec -->
</FrequencyType>
```

**Rate Restriction:**
```xml
<RateRestrictionType>
  <RateLock>Y|N</RateLock> - Prevent rate changes
  <RateRange>
    <Amount>
      <Min>
      <Max>
    </Amount>
    <Percent>
      <Min>
      <Max>
    </Percent>
    <RangeLock>Y|N</RangeLock>
  </RateRange>
</RateRestrictionType>
```

**Key Structure:**
Defines what transactions a fee applies to (1-4 keys per fee):
```xml
<KeyStructureType>
  <Key>Value1</Key>
  <Key>Value2</Key>
  <Key>Value3</Key>
  <Key>Value4</Key>
</KeyStructureType>
```

Valid key structures are maintained in the **PPM Key Structure File** (updated periodically).

### Common.xsd
**Purpose:** Base entity types

**Hierarchy Identifiers:**

```xml
<BankNumType> - 4 digits (e.g., 1234)

<AssocNumType> - 6 digits
<MerchantNumType> - 2-16 digits
<AgentNumType> - 6 digits
```

**Hierarchy Levels:**
- 220 - Client
- 200 - Bank

- 100 - Merchant

## 3. Pricing Configuration Workflow

### Step 1: Merchant Must Exist in Express
**Prerequisites:**
- Merchant boarded in TSYS Express system
- Bank Number assigned
- Merchant Number generated
- Merchant status = Boarded (B)

**Critical:** PPM will **reject** any SaveMerchantPricing request if the merchant does not exist in the billing system.

### Step 2: Create Merchant Pricing Profile

**Operation:** SaveMerchantPricing

**Process Flow:**
```
1. Submit MerchantPricingRequest
   > Validates merchant exists in system
   > Validates profile data
   > Creates/overwrites profile
   > Returns profile status

2. If fees included:
   > Validates each fee item
   > Checks key structure validity
   > Verifies fee category rules
   > Ensures limits not exceeded (80 direct + 80 inherited per hierarchy level)
   > Returns fee-level outcomes

3. Response:
   > Overall Status (success/failure)
   > ProfileStatus (boarding status)
   > Per-fee Outcome tags
   > Mirror of submitted data with status indicators
```

**Profile Limits:**
- 80 fee items directly on merchant profile
- 80 additional fee items can be inherited from each hierarchy level (bank/group/association)
- Total potential: 320 fee items per merchant
- ERGs: Up to 100 fee items
- Key structures: Up to 4,000 per profile/ERG

### Step 3: Configure Fee Items

**Fee Creation Methods:**

**A. SaveMerchantPricing (Full Profile)**
- Creates new profile or completely replaces existing
- Removes all existing fees and replaces with new set
- Use for: Initial setup, complete pricing overhaul

**B. AddMerchantFees (Incremental)**
- Adds new fees without affecting existing
- Use for: Adding new fee categories, expanding pricing

**C. ModifyMerchantFees (Targeted Updates)**
- Updates specific fees by FeeIdentity
- Existing fees not mentioned remain unchanged
- **Important:** Matching StartDate required to update specific effective rate
- Non-matching future StartDate erases subsequent effective rates
- Use for: Rate adjustments, date changes

**D. ApplyTemplatesToMerchant**
- Applies pre-configured pricing templates
- Templates can be at Client/Bank/Group/Association levels
- Use for: Standardized pricing deployment

### Step 4: Configure DDA Accounts

**Operation:** SaveMerchantDDA

```xml
<MerchantDDARequest>
  <Merchant>
    <BankNum>1234</BankNum>
    <MerchantNum>123456789</MerchantNum>
  </Merchant>
  <DdaAccount>
    <TranType>P</TranType> <!-- Primary -->
    <AccountType>C</AccountType> <!-- Checking -->
    <DdaNumber>123456789</DdaNumber>
    <TransitRouting>121000248</TransitRouting>
  </DdaAccount>
  <DdaAccount>
    <TranType>C</TranType> <!-- Chargebacks -->
    <AccountType>C</AccountType>
    <DdaNumber>987654321</DdaNumber>
    <TransitRouting>121000248</TransitRouting>
  </DdaAccount>
</MerchantDDARequest>
```

### Step 5: Optional ERG Assignment

**If tracking expenses:**
1. Create ERG: AddErg operation
2. Add expense fees: AddErgFees
3. Link to merchant: SaveMerchantPricing with ErgId element

### Step 6: Validation & Activation

**GetMerchantPricing operation:**
- Retrieves complete profile
- Returns all active fees (current + future)
- Returns current month expired fees
- Does NOT return expired fees from previous months
- Includes hierarchical fee items
- Does NOT include ERG expenses (use GetErg separately)

**Fee Status Indicators:**
- **Complete** (C) - Fee fully configured and active
- **Work In Progress** (WIP) - Fee partially configured (GUI only)
- XML-submitted fees always saved as Complete

## 5. Integration Patterns and Best Practices

### A. Express to PPM Integration Pattern

**Step-by-Step Integration:**

```typescript
// 1. Create Express Account
const expressResponse = await createExpressAccount({
  merchantName: mpaData.businessLegalName,
  dbaName: mpaData.dbaName,

});

// 2. Extract Express Identifiers

// 3. Wait for Boarding Confirmation

// 4. Configure PPM Pricing

    bankNum: bankNumber,

  },

// 5. Configure DDA

// 6. Validate Setup
```

### B. Error Handling Patterns

**Response Validation:**
```typescript
interface PPMResponse {
  responseMetaData: {
    code: number;
    description: string;
  };
  merchantPricing: {
    profileStatus: {
      code: number;
      description: string;
    };
    fees: Array<{
      outcome: {
        code: number;
        description: string;
      };
    }>;
  };
}

// Check overall response
if (response.responseMetaData.code !== 0) {
  throw new PPMError(response.responseMetaData.description);
}

// Check profile status
if (response.merchantPricing.profileStatus.code !== 0) {
  throw new ProfileError(response.merchantPricing.profileStatus.description);
}

// Check individual fee outcomes
const failedFees = response.merchantPricing.fees
  .filter(fee => fee.outcome.code !== 0);

if (failedFees.length > 0) {
  // Handle partial success
  logFailedFees(failedFees);
}
```

**Common Error Codes:**
- Code 0 - Success
- Merchant not found - Merchant doesn't exist in billing system
- Invalid key structure - Key combination not in PPM Key Structure File
- Fee limit exceeded - More than 80 direct fees on profile
- Invalid fee category - Business rule violation for fee category
- Duplicate fee - Fee with same identity already exists
- Invalid date range - StartDate after StopDate or expired dates

```typescript
// Transform MPA discount rates to PPM discount fees
function transformDiscountFees(mpaData: MPAData): PPMFee[] {
  const fees: PPMFee[] = [];
  
  // Visa Credit
  if (mpaData.pricing.visaCreditDiscountRate) {
    fees.push({
      feeIdentity: {
        category: 12, // Discount
        name: 'Visa Credit Discount'
      },
      keyStructure: {
        keys: ['VISA', 'CREDIT']
      },
      pricing: {
        percentWithPerItem: {
          dateRate: {
            startDate: formatDate(new Date()),
            stopDate: '12/31/9999',
            percent: mpaData.pricing.visaCreditDiscountRate,
            amount: mpaData.pricing.visaCreditPerTxnFee || 0,
            countChargeType: 'G',
            amountChargeType: 'G'
          }
        }
      }
    });
  }
  
  // Mastercard Credit
  if (mpaData.pricing.mcCreditDiscountRate) {
    fees.push({
      feeIdentity: {
        category: 12,
        name: 'MC Credit Discount'
      },
      keyStructure: {
        keys: ['MC', 'CREDIT']
      },
      pricing: {
        percentWithPerItem: {
          dateRate: {
            startDate: formatDate(new Date()),
            stopDate: '12/31/9999',
            percent: mpaData.pricing.mcCreditDiscountRate,
            amount: mpaData.pricing.mcCreditPerTxnFee || 0,
            countChargeType: 'G',
            amountChargeType: 'G'
          }
        }
      }
    });
  }
  
  return fees;
}

// Transform monthly fees
function transformMonthlyFees(mpaData: MPAData): PPMFee[] {
  const fees: PPMFee[] = [];
  
  if (mpaData.pricing.monthlyAccountFee) {
    fees.push({
      feeIdentity: {
        category: 9, // MISC Fixed
        name: 'Monthly Account Fee'
      },
      keyStructure: {
        keys: ['MONTHLY']
      },
      frequency: allMonths(), // Y for all 12 months
      pricing: {
        fixedRate: {
          dateRate: {
            startDate: formatDate(new Date()),
            stopDate: '12/31/9999',
            amount: mpaData.pricing.monthlyAccountFee
          }
        }
      }
    });
  }
  
  return fees;
}
```

### D. Rate Update Patterns

**Modifying Existing Rates:**
```typescript
// Safe rate update - matches existing start date
async function updateExistingRate(
  bankNum: string,
  merchantNum: string,
  feeName: string,
  newRate: number
) {
  // 1. Get current pricing
  const current = await getMerchantPricing(bankNum, merchantNum);
  
  // 2. Find fee to update
  const fee = current.fees.find(f => f.feeIdentity.name === feeName);
  if (!fee) throw new Error('Fee not found');
  
  // 3. Get current effective rate
  const currentRate = fee.pricing.percentWithPerItem.dateRate;
  
  // 4. Modify with SAME start date to update in place
  await modifyMerchantFees({
    merchant: { bankNum, merchantNum },
    fees: [{
      feeIdentity: fee.feeIdentity,
      pricing: {
        percentWithPerItem: {
          dateRate: {
            startDate: currentRate.startDate, // MUST MATCH
            stopDate: currentRate.stopDate,
            percent: newRate,
            amount: currentRate.amount,
            countChargeType: currentRate.countChargeType,
            amountChargeType: currentRate.amountChargeType
          }
        }
      }
    }]
  });
}

// Schedule future rate change
async function scheduleFutureRate(
  bankNum: string,
  merchantNum: string,
  feeName: string,
  effectiveDate: Date,
  newRate: number
) {
  const current = await getMerchantPricing(bankNum, merchantNum);
  const fee = current.fees.find(f => f.feeIdentity.name === feeName);
  
  // Add new effective rate
  await modifyMerchantFees({
    merchant: { bankNum, merchantNum },
    fees: [{
      feeIdentity: fee.feeIdentity,
      pricing: {
        percentWithPerItem: {
          dateRate: {
            startDate: formatDate(effectiveDate), // NEW DATE
            stopDate: '12/31/9999',
            percent: newRate,
            // ... other fields
          }
        }
      }
    }]
  });
}
```

### E. Batch Processing Patterns

**Bulk Merchant Setup:**
```typescript
// Generate batch request file
function generateMerchantPricingBatch(
  merchants: Array<{ bankNum: string; merchantNum: string; pricing: any }>
): string {
  const batchRequests = merchants.map(m => 
    createSaveMerchantPricingXML(m)

// Upload to mailbox
async function submitBatch(
  batchXML: string,
  clientShortName: string,
  batchId: string
): Promise<string> {
  const filename = `${clientShortName}_MerchantPricingReq_${batchId}.xml`;
  
  await uploadToMailbox(filename, batchXML);
  
  return filename;
}

// Poll for response
async function waitForBatchResponse(
  requestFilename: string
): Promise<BatchResponse> {
  const responseFilename = requestFilename.replace('Req', 'Res');
  
  let attempts = 0;
  while (attempts < 30) { // 30 attempts = ~15 minutes
    const response = await checkMailbox(responseFilename);
    if (response) {
      return parseBatchResponse(response);
    }
    await sleep(30000); // Wait 30 seconds
    attempts++;
  }
  
  throw new Error('Batch response timeout');
}
```

### F. Key Structure Management

**Key Structure Validation:**
```typescript
// Load and cache valid key structures
class KeyStructureValidator {
  private validKeys: Map<number, Set<string[]>>;
  
  async loadKeyStructures() {
    // Load from PPM Key Structure File
    const keyFile = await fetchPPMKeyStructureFile();
    this.validKeys = parseKeyStructureFile(keyFile);
  }
  
  validateKeyStructure(
    category: number,
    keys: string[]
  ): boolean {
    const validKeysForCategory = this.validKeys.get(category);
    if (!validKeysForCategory) return false;
    
    return validKeysForCategory.has(keys.join('|'));
  }
  
  suggestValidKeys(category: number): string[][] {
    return Array.from(this.validKeys.get(category) || [])
      .map(k => k.split('|'));
  }
}
```

## 7. Relationship Between PPM and Express

### Integration Architecture

```

                     TSYS Ecosystem                           

                                                               
                    
    TSYS Express                    PPM                 
    (Merchant                   (Pricing &              
     Boarding)                   Billing)               
                    
                                                           
            Creates                     Configures         
             Bank Number                Fee Items        
             Merchant Number            Rate Schedules   
             Account Status             DDA Accounts     
                                         ERGs             
                                                           
                               
                                                            
                  Merchant ID                                
                  (BankNum + MerchantNum)                   
                                                            
                                  
             Billing/Statement                            
                 System                                   
                                  
                                                              

```

### Key Relationships

**1. Merchant Identity:**
- Express creates the merchant record and assigns BankNum + MerchantNum
- PPM references merchants by BankNum + MerchantNum
- **PPM cannot create merchants** - they must exist in Express first

**2. Data Dependencies:**

| Express Data | PPM Requirement | Notes |
|--------------|-----------------|-------|
| Merchant Number | Required | Primary identifier for PPM operations |
| Bank Number | Required | Hierarchy level identifier |
| Boarding Status | Must be "B" (Boarded) | PPM rejects if merchant not boarded |
| DBA Name | Optional reference | For PPM reporting |
| MCC | Optional reference | Can influence fee categories |

**3. Operational Sequence:**

```
Step 1: Express - Create Merchant Account
    Returns: BankNum, MerchantNum
   
Step 2: Express - Complete Boarding Process
    Status changes to "B" (Boarded)
   
Step 3: PPM - SaveMerchantPricing (NOW ALLOWED)
    Creates pricing profile
   
Step 4: PPM - SaveMerchantDDA
    Configures settlement accounts
   
Step 5: Billing System - Generates Statements
    Uses PPM pricing + Express merchant data
```

**4. Shared Data Elements:**

**Merchant Identification (Both Systems):**
- BankNum (4 digits)
- MerchantNum (2-16 digits)

**Express-Only Data:**
- Legal Name, DBA
- Tax ID
- Business Address
- Owner Information
- MCC
- Processing Limits

**PPM-Only Data:**
- Fee Items
- Pricing Rates
- ERG Assignments
- Agent Assignments (for RP)
- Minimum Discount
- Rate Restrictions

**Shared/Referenced:**
- DDA Account Numbers (Express creates, PPM references)
- Bank routing numbers
- Merchant status

**5. Error Handling:**

If PPM receives a request for non-existent merchant:
```xml
<Response>
  <ResponseMetaData>
    <Code>ERROR_CODE</Code>
    <Description>Merchant not found in billing system</Description>
  </ResponseMetaData>
</Response>
```

Resolution: Ensure merchant exists in Express and is boarded before calling PPM.

### B. Data Validation Strategy

**1. Pre-submission Validation:**
```typescript
interface ValidationRule {
  field: string;
  validate: (value: any) => boolean;
  message: string;
}

const merchantPricingRules: ValidationRule[] = [
  {
    field: 'merchant.bankNum',
    validate: (v) => /^\d{4}$/.test(v),
    message: 'Bank number must be 4 digits'
  },
  {
    field: 'merchant.merchantNum',
    validate: (v) => /^\d{2,16}$/.test(v),
    message: 'Merchant number must be 2-16 digits'
  },
  // ... more rules
];

function validatePPMRequest(request: any): ValidationResult {
  const errors: string[] = [];
  
  for (const rule of merchantPricingRules) {
    const value = getNestedValue(request, rule.field);
    if (!rule.validate(value)) {
      errors.push(rule.message);
    }
  }
  
  return { valid: errors.length === 0, errors };
}
```

**2. Key Structure Validation:**
```typescript
// Load valid key structures on startup
const keyStructureCache = new Map<number, Set<string>>();

async function loadKeyStructures() {
  // Fetch from PPM Key Structure File or cached version
  const structures = await fetchPPMKeyStructures();
  
  for (const [category, keys] of structures) {
    keyStructureCache.set(
      category,
      new Set(keys.map(k => k.join('|')))
    );
  }
}

function validateKeyStructure(
  category: number,
  keys: string[]
): boolean {
  const validKeys = keyStructureCache.get(category);
  if (!validKeys) return false;
  
  return validKeys.has(keys.join('|'));
}
```

### D. Monitoring and Logging

**1. Comprehensive Logging:**
```typescript
interface PPMOperationLog {
  operation: string;
  timestamp: Date;
  bankNum: string;
  merchantNum: string;
  requestSize: number;
  responseCode: number;
  responseTime: number;
  errors?: string[];
}

async function loggedPPMOperation<T>(
  operation: string,
  request: any,
  execute: () => Promise<T>
): Promise<T> {
  const startTime = Date.now();
  const log: PPMOperationLog = {
    operation,
    timestamp: new Date(),
    bankNum: request.merchant?.bankNum,
    merchantNum: request.merchant?.merchantNum,
    requestSize: JSON.stringify(request).length,
    responseCode: 0,
    responseTime: 0
  };
  
  try {
    const result = await execute();
    log.responseCode = result.responseMetaData?.code || 0;
    log.responseTime = Date.now() - startTime;
    
    // Log to database/monitoring system
    await saveOperationLog(log);
    
    return result;
  } catch (error) {
    log.responseCode = -1;
    log.responseTime = Date.now() - startTime;
    log.errors = [error.message];
    
    await saveOperationLog(log);
    throw error;
  }
}
```

## Summary of Critical Integration Points

### 1. **Prerequisites**
- Merchant must exist in TSYS Express
- Merchant must be boarded (status = "B")
- BankNum and MerchantNum must be obtained from Express

### 2. **Primary Operations**
- **SaveMerchantPricing** - Initial pricing setup after Express boarding
- **AddMerchantFees** - Incremental fee additions
- **ModifyMerchantFees** - Rate updates (careful with date matching)
- **GetMerchantPricing** - Validation and retrieval
- **SaveMerchantDDA** - Bank account configuration

### 3. **Data Transformation Requirements**
- MPA discount rates  PPM Discount fees (Category 12)
- MPA monthly fees  PPM MISC Fixed fees (Category 9)
- MPA transaction fees  PPM Auth/Data Capture fees (Categories 1, 3)
- MPA bank account  PPM DDA configuration

### 4. **Critical Business Rules**
- Fee items limited to 80 direct + 80 per hierarchy level
- Key structures must be in valid combinations
- Date ranges: StartDate cannot be in past for new fees
- Effective rates require StopDate on all but final rate
- XML-submitted fees always saved as Complete status

### 5. **Error Handling**
- Check ResponseMetaData.Code (0 = success)
- Check ProfileStatus.Code for profile-level errors
- Check individual Fee.Outcome.Code for fee-level errors
- Log all failed operations for audit trail

# TSYS Portfolio Pricing Manager (PPM) XML SDK - Comprehensive Analysis Report

## Executive Summary

TSYS Portfolio Pricing Manager (PPM) is a pricing and billing management system that enables clients to configure merchant pricing, track expenses, and manage fee structures for their merchant portfolios. The system integrates with TSYS Express (merchant account creation) and operates through both a web-based GUI and XML API interfaces.

**Critical Integration Flow:**
```
Express Account Creation  PPM Pricing Configuration  Statement/Billing Integration
```

The merchant must exist in TSYS's boarding system (via Express) **before** PPM pricing can be configured.

## 1. Main API Operations: Batch vs Real-Time

### Real-Time Operations (WSDL-based)

**Location:** `/Users/coreyyoung/Desktop/Projects/tsyscrm/TSYS-DOCS/PPM-XML-WSDLSchemas-RealTime/MerchantPricingService.wsdl`

PPM provides a comprehensive SOAP-based web service with the following operation categories:

#### Merchant Pricing Operations
- **SaveMerchantPricing** - Creates new or overwrites existing merchant pricing profile
- **GetMerchantPricing** - Retrieves merchant pricing profile and all associated fees
- **DeleteMerchantPricing** - Removes merchant pricing profile entirely
- **AddMerchantFees** - Adds new fees to existing profile without affecting others
- **ModifyMerchantFees** - Updates specific existing fees
- **AddOrModifyMerchantFees** - Combined operation for adding or modifying fees
- **DeleteMerchantFees** - Removes specific fees from profile
- **ModifyMerchantFeesFrequencyAndRates** - Updates only frequency and rate information
- **ApplyTemplatesToMerchant** - Applies pre-configured pricing templates
- **ReassignTemplateToMerchant** - Changes template assignment

#### Hierarchy Pricing Operations
- **SaveHierarchyPricing** - Creates/updates pricing at bank, group, or association level
- **GetHierarchyPricing** - Retrieves hierarchical pricing structures
- **DeleteHierarchyPricing** - Removes hierarchical pricing
- **AddHierarchyFees** - Adds fees to hierarchy level
- **ModifyHierarchyFees** - Updates hierarchy fees

#### ERG (Expense Rate Group) Operations
- **AddErg** - Creates new expense rate group

#### RP (Relationship Profitability) Operations
- **AddRpErg** - Creates RP expense rate group for agent commissions
- **ModifyRpErg** - Updates RP ERG
- **DeleteRpErg** - Removes RP ERG
- **GetRpErg** - Retrieves RP ERG details
- **AddRpErgFees** - Adds RP fees
- **ModifyRpErgFees** - Updates RP fees
- **DeleteRpErgFees** - Removes RP fees
- **AddRpAgent** - Creates agent profile
- **ModifyRpAgent** - Updates agent
- **DeleteRpAgent** - Removes agent
- **GetRpAgent** - Retrieves agent details

#### DDA (Direct Deposit Account) Operations
- **SaveMerchantDDA** - Configures merchant bank account information
- **GetMerchantDDA** - Retrieves DDA details
- **DeleteMerchantDDA** - Removes DDA configuration

**Schemas:**

#### Batch Processing Characteristics

**Delivery Method:**
- Files uploaded to client-specific mailbox
- Processed multiple times per day (schedule TBD during implementation)
- Response files returned to same mailbox

**File Naming Convention:**
```
ClientShortName_RequestGroupType_BatchID_XXXX.xml
```

**Request Group Types:**

## 2. Key XML Schemas

### MerchantPricing.xsd
**Purpose:** Core merchant pricing profile structure

**Key Types:**
```xml
<MerchantPricingRequestType>
  <Merchant> - Identification (BankNum, MerchantNum)
  <Agent> - Optional RP agent (6-digit code)
  <ErgId> - Optional expense rate group link
  <MinimumDiscount> - Minimum monthly charge configuration
  <Fees> - Collection of fee items
</MerchantPricingRequestType>
```

**MinimumDiscount Structure:**
- **Amount** - Minimum charge amount
- **StartDate** / **StopDate** - Effective date range
- **BillingMethod** - D (Deduct) or R (Reverse)
- **Frequency** - Monthly flags (Jan-Dec)
- **RateRestriction** - Rate locks and ranges
- **GLItemCode** / **UserDataCode** - Accounting codes

**Boarding Status Codes:**
- P - Pending
- B - Boarded
- D - Deactivated
- C - Closed

### ProfilePricing.xsd
**Purpose:** Fee item structures and pricing configurations

**Fee Categories (1-15):**
1. Authorization Transactions
2. Authorization Other
3. Data Capture Transactions
4. Data Capture Other
5. Exceptions
6. Debit Network
7. EBT (Electronic Benefits Transfer)
8. MISC Per Item Fees
9. MISC Fixed Fees
10. Interchange
11. Individual Plan
12. Discount
13. Card Brand Fees
15. Transaction Method

**FeeRequestType Structure:**
```xml
<Fee>
  <FeeIdentity>
    <Category> - Fee category (1-15)
    <Name> - Fee name (30 chars max)
    <ModifiedName> - Optional alternate name
  </FeeIdentity>
  <TemplateIdentity> - Optional template reference
  <KeyStructure> - 1-4 key values defining fee applicability
  <DdaAccountOverride> - Optional account override
  <Frequency> - Monthly application flags
  <Setting> - Tax, billing, GL/User codes
  <StatementSetting> - Display preferences
  <Pricing> - Rate configuration
  <RateRestriction> - Rate locks/ranges
</Fee>
```

**Pricing Methods:**
- **Per Item** - Fixed amount per transaction
- **Percentage** - Percentage of transaction amount
- **Volume Tiered** - Different rates based on volume thresholds
  - Pick-a-Tier (P) - Single tier applies
  - Fill-a-Tier (F) - Progressive tiers
- **Pass-Through** - Interchange pass-through + markup
- **Differential** - Interchange differential pricing

**Tier Configuration:**
```xml
<VolumeTier>
  <TierType>V</TierType> <!-- Volume -->
  <VolumeTierMethod>P or F</VolumeTierMethod>
  <VolumeTierBasedOn>
    A - Amount
    N - Number of transactions
    V - Average ticket
    P - Percentage of total
  </VolumeTierBasedOn>
  <Rates>
    <DateRate>
      <StartDate>
      <StopDate>
      <Tiers>
        <Tier>
          <MinFactor> - Threshold amount/count
          <Amount> - Per-item rate
          <Percent> - Percentage rate
        </Tier>
      </Tiers>
    </DateRate>
  </Rates>
</VolumeTier>
```

**Effective Rate Scheduling:**
Multiple DateRate elements allow scheduling future rate changes:
```xml
<Pricing>
  <DateRate>
    <StartDate>06/01/2015</StartDate>
    <StopDate>06/30/2015</StopDate>
    <Percent>1.00</Percent>
  </DateRate>
  <DateRate>
    <StartDate>07/01/2015</StartDate>
    <StopDate>07/31/2015</StopDate>
    <Percent>1.20</Percent>
  </DateRate>
</Pricing>
```

## 3. Pricing Configuration Workflow

### Step 1: Merchant Must Exist in Express
**Prerequisites:**
- Merchant boarded in TSYS Express system
- Bank Number assigned
- Merchant Number generated
- Merchant status = Boarded (B)

**Critical:** PPM will **reject** any SaveMerchantPricing request if the merchant does not exist in the billing system.

### Step 2: Create Merchant Pricing Profile

**Operation:** SaveMerchantPricing

**Process Flow:**
```
1. Submit MerchantPricingRequest
   > Validates merchant exists in system
   > Validates profile data
   > Creates/overwrites profile
   > Returns profile status

2. If fees included:
   > Validates each fee item
   > Checks key structure validity
   > Verifies fee category rules
   > Ensures limits not exceeded (80 direct + 80 inherited per hierarchy level)
   > Returns fee-level outcomes

3. Response:
   > Overall Status (success/failure)
   > ProfileStatus (boarding status)
   > Per-fee Outcome tags
   > Mirror of submitted data with status indicators
```

**Profile Limits:**
- 80 fee items directly on merchant profile
- 80 additional fee items can be inherited from each hierarchy level (bank/group/association)
- Total potential: 320 fee items per merchant
- ERGs: Up to 100 fee items
- Key structures: Up to 4,000 per profile/ERG

### Step 3: Configure Fee Items

**Fee Creation Methods:**

**A. SaveMerchantPricing (Full Profile)**
- Creates new profile or completely replaces existing
- Removes all existing fees and replaces with new set
- Use for: Initial setup, complete pricing overhaul

**B. AddMerchantFees (Incremental)**
- Adds new fees without affecting existing
- Use for: Adding new fee categories, expanding pricing

**C. ModifyMerchantFees (Targeted Updates)**
- Updates specific fees by FeeIdentity
- Existing fees not mentioned remain unchanged
- **Important:** Matching StartDate required to update specific effective rate
- Non-matching future StartDate erases subsequent effective rates
- Use for: Rate adjustments, date changes

**D. ApplyTemplatesToMerchant**
- Applies pre-configured pricing templates
- Templates can be at Client/Bank/Group/Association levels
- Use for: Standardized pricing deployment

### Step 4: Configure DDA Accounts

**Operation:** SaveMerchantDDA

```xml
<MerchantDDARequest>
  <Merchant>
    <BankNum>1234</BankNum>
    <MerchantNum>123456789</MerchantNum>
  </Merchant>
  <DdaAccount>
    <TranType>P</TranType> <!-- Primary -->
    <AccountType>C</AccountType> <!-- Checking -->
    <DdaNumber>123456789</DdaNumber>
    <TransitRouting>121000248</TransitRouting>
  </DdaAccount>
  <DdaAccount>
    <TranType>C</TranType> <!-- Chargebacks -->
    <AccountType>C</AccountType>
    <DdaNumber>987654321</DdaNumber>
    <TransitRouting>121000248</TransitRouting>
  </DdaAccount>
</MerchantDDARequest>
```

### Step 5: Optional ERG Assignment

**If tracking expenses:**
1. Create ERG: AddErg operation
2. Add expense fees: AddErgFees
3. Link to merchant: SaveMerchantPricing with ErgId element

### Step 6: Validation & Activation

**GetMerchantPricing operation:**
- Retrieves complete profile
- Returns all active fees (current + future)
- Returns current month expired fees
- Does NOT return expired fees from previous months
- Includes hierarchical fee items
- Does NOT include ERG expenses (use GetErg separately)

**Fee Status Indicators:**
- **Complete** (C) - Fee fully configured and active
- **Work In Progress** (WIP) - Fee partially configured (GUI only)
- XML-submitted fees always saved as Complete

```xml
            <FeeIdentity>
              <Category>10</Category> <!-- Interchange -->
              <Name>Interchange Pass Through</Name>
            </FeeIdentity>
            <KeyStructure>
              <Key>VISA</Key>
              <Key>ALL</Key>
            </KeyStructure>
            <Frequency>
              <Jan>Y</Jan><Feb>Y</Feb><Mar>Y</Mar>
              <Apr>Y</Apr><May>Y</May><Jun>Y</Jun>
              <Jul>Y</Jul><Aug>Y</Aug><Sep>Y</Sep>
              <Oct>Y</Oct><Nov>Y</Nov><Dec>Y</Dec>
            </Frequency>
            <Pricing>
              <PassThrough>
                <DateRate>
                  <StartDate>01/01/2024</StartDate>
                  <StopDate>12/31/9999</StopDate>
                  <Percent>0.10</Percent> <!-- Markup -->
                  <Amount>0.02</Amount> <!-- Per-item markup -->
                  <CountChargeType>G</CountChargeType>
                  <AmountChargeType>G</AmountChargeType>
                </DateRate>
              </PassThrough>
            </Pricing>
          </Fee>
        </Fees>
      </MerchantPricing>
    </MerchantPricingRequest>
  </soapenv:Body>
</soapenv:Envelope>
```

### A. Express to PPM Integration Pattern

**Step-by-Step Integration:**


### B. Error Handling Patterns

**Response Validation:**
```typescript
interface PPMResponse {
  responseMetaData: {
    code: number;
    description: string;
  };
  merchantPricing: {
    profileStatus: {
      code: number;
      description: string;
    };
    fees: Array<{
      outcome: {
        code: number;
        description: string;
      };
    }>;
  };
}

// Check overall response
if (response.responseMetaData.code !== 0) {
  throw new PPMError(response.responseMetaData.description);
}

// Check profile status
if (response.merchantPricing.profileStatus.code !== 0) {
  throw new ProfileError(response.merchantPricing.profileStatus.description);
}

// Check individual fee outcomes
const failedFees = response.merchantPricing.fees
  .filter(fee => fee.outcome.code !== 0);

if (failedFees.length > 0) {
  // Handle partial success
  logFailedFees(failedFees);
}
```

**Common Error Codes:**
- Code 0 - Success
- Merchant not found - Merchant doesn't exist in billing system
- Invalid key structure - Key combination not in PPM Key Structure File
- Fee limit exceeded - More than 80 direct fees on profile
- Invalid fee category - Business rule violation for fee category
- Duplicate fee - Fee with same identity already exists
- Invalid date range - StartDate after StopDate or expired dates

**MPA to PPM Fee Mapping:**
```typescript
// Transform MPA discount rates to PPM discount fees
function transformDiscountFees(mpaData: MPAData): PPMFee[] {
  const fees: PPMFee[] = [];
  
  // Visa Credit
  if (mpaData.pricing.visaCreditDiscountRate) {
    fees.push({
      feeIdentity: {
        category: 12, // Discount
        name: 'Visa Credit Discount'
      },
      keyStructure: {
        keys: ['VISA', 'CREDIT']
      },
      pricing: {
        percentWithPerItem: {
          dateRate: {
            startDate: formatDate(new Date()),
            stopDate: '12/31/9999',
            percent: mpaData.pricing.visaCreditDiscountRate,
            amount: mpaData.pricing.visaCreditPerTxnFee || 0,
            countChargeType: 'G',
            amountChargeType: 'G'
          }
        }
      }
    });
  }
  
  // Mastercard Credit
  if (mpaData.pricing.mcCreditDiscountRate) {
    fees.push({
      feeIdentity: {
        category: 12,
        name: 'MC Credit Discount'
      },
      keyStructure: {
        keys: ['MC', 'CREDIT']
      },
      pricing: {
        percentWithPerItem: {
          dateRate: {
            startDate: formatDate(new Date()),
            stopDate: '12/31/9999',
            percent: mpaData.pricing.mcCreditDiscountRate,
            amount: mpaData.pricing.mcCreditPerTxnFee || 0,
            countChargeType: 'G',
            amountChargeType: 'G'
          }
        }
      }
    });
  }
  
  return fees;
}

// Transform monthly fees
function transformMonthlyFees(mpaData: MPAData): PPMFee[] {
  const fees: PPMFee[] = [];
  
  if (mpaData.pricing.monthlyAccountFee) {
    fees.push({
      feeIdentity: {
        category: 9, // MISC Fixed
        name: 'Monthly Account Fee'
      },
      keyStructure: {
        keys: ['MONTHLY']
      },
      frequency: allMonths(), // Y for all 12 months
      pricing: {
        fixedRate: {
          dateRate: {
            startDate: formatDate(new Date()),
            stopDate: '12/31/9999',
            amount: mpaData.pricing.monthlyAccountFee
          }
        }
      }
    });
  }
  
  return fees;
}
```

### D. Rate Update Patterns

**Modifying Existing Rates:**
```typescript
// Safe rate update - matches existing start date
async function updateExistingRate(
  bankNum: string,
  merchantNum: string,
  feeName: string,
  newRate: number
) {
  // 1. Get current pricing
  const current = await getMerchantPricing(bankNum, merchantNum);
  
  // 2. Find fee to update
  const fee = current.fees.find(f => f.feeIdentity.name === feeName);
  if (!fee) throw new Error('Fee not found');
  
  // 3. Get current effective rate
  const currentRate = fee.pricing.percentWithPerItem.dateRate;
  
  // 4. Modify with SAME start date to update in place
  await modifyMerchantFees({
    merchant: { bankNum, merchantNum },
    fees: [{
      feeIdentity: fee.feeIdentity,
      pricing: {
        percentWithPerItem: {
          dateRate: {
            startDate: currentRate.startDate, // MUST MATCH
            stopDate: currentRate.stopDate,
            percent: newRate,
            amount: currentRate.amount,
            countChargeType: currentRate.countChargeType,
            amountChargeType: currentRate.amountChargeType
          }
        }
      }
    }]
  });
}

// Schedule future rate change
async function scheduleFutureRate(
  bankNum: string,
  merchantNum: string,
  feeName: string,
  effectiveDate: Date,
  newRate: number
) {
  const current = await getMerchantPricing(bankNum, merchantNum);
  const fee = current.fees.find(f => f.feeIdentity.name === feeName);
  
  // Add new effective rate
  await modifyMerchantFees({
    merchant: { bankNum, merchantNum },
    fees: [{
      feeIdentity: fee.feeIdentity,
      pricing: {
        percentWithPerItem: {
          dateRate: {
            startDate: formatDate(effectiveDate), // NEW DATE
            stopDate: '12/31/9999',
            percent: newRate,
            // ... other fields
          }
        }
      }
    }]
  });
}
```

### E. Batch Processing Patterns

**Bulk Merchant Setup:**
```typescript
// Generate batch request file
function generateMerchantPricingBatch(
  merchants: Array<{ bankNum: string; merchantNum: string; pricing: any }>
): string {
  const batchRequests = merchants.map(m => 
    createSaveMerchantPricingXML(m)
  );

}

// Upload to mailbox
async function submitBatch(
  batchXML: string,
  clientShortName: string,
  batchId: string
): Promise<string> {
  const filename = `${clientShortName}_MerchantPricingReq_${batchId}.xml`;
  
  await uploadToMailbox(filename, batchXML);
  
  return filename;
}

// Poll for response
async function waitForBatchResponse(
  requestFilename: string
): Promise<BatchResponse> {
  const responseFilename = requestFilename.replace('Req', 'Res');
  
  let attempts = 0;
  while (attempts < 30) { // 30 attempts = ~15 minutes
    const response = await checkMailbox(responseFilename);
    if (response) {
      return parseBatchResponse(response);
    }
    await sleep(30000); // Wait 30 seconds
    attempts++;
  }
  
  throw new Error('Batch response timeout');
}
```

### F. Key Structure Management

**Key Structure Validation:**
```typescript
// Load and cache valid key structures
class KeyStructureValidator {
  private validKeys: Map<number, Set<string[]>>;
  
  async loadKeyStructures() {
    // Load from PPM Key Structure File
    const keyFile = await fetchPPMKeyStructureFile();
    this.validKeys = parseKeyStructureFile(keyFile);
  }
  
  validateKeyStructure(
    category: number,
    keys: string[]
  ): boolean {
    const validKeysForCategory = this.validKeys.get(category);
    if (!validKeysForCategory) return false;
    
    return validKeysForCategory.has(keys.join('|'));
  }
  
  suggestValidKeys(category: number): string[][] {
    return Array.from(this.validKeys.get(category) || [])
      .map(k => k.split('|'));
  }
}
```

## 7. Relationship Between PPM and Express

### Integration Architecture

```

                     TSYS Ecosystem                           

                                                               
                    
    TSYS Express                    PPM                 
    (Merchant                   (Pricing &              
     Boarding)                   Billing)               
                    
                                                           
            Creates                     Configures         
             Bank Number                Fee Items        
             Merchant Number            Rate Schedules   
             Account Status             DDA Accounts     
                                         ERGs             
                                                           
                               
                                                            
                  Merchant ID                                
                  (BankNum + MerchantNum)                   
                                                            
                                  
             Billing/Statement                            
                 System                                   
                                  
                                                              

```

### Key Relationships

**1. Merchant Identity:**
- Express creates the merchant record and assigns BankNum + MerchantNum
- PPM references merchants by BankNum + MerchantNum
- **PPM cannot create merchants** - they must exist in Express first

**2. Data Dependencies:**

| Express Data | PPM Requirement | Notes |
|--------------|-----------------|-------|
| Merchant Number | Required | Primary identifier for PPM operations |
| Bank Number | Required | Hierarchy level identifier |
| Boarding Status | Must be "B" (Boarded) | PPM rejects if merchant not boarded |
| DBA Name | Optional reference | For PPM reporting |
| MCC | Optional reference | Can influence fee categories |

**3. Operational Sequence:**

```
Step 1: Express - Create Merchant Account
    Returns: BankNum, MerchantNum
   
Step 2: Express - Complete Boarding Process
    Status changes to "B" (Boarded)
   
Step 3: PPM - SaveMerchantPricing (NOW ALLOWED)
    Creates pricing profile
   
Step 4: PPM - SaveMerchantDDA
    Configures settlement accounts
   
Step 5: Billing System - Generates Statements
    Uses PPM pricing + Express merchant data
```

**4. Shared Data Elements:**

**Merchant Identification (Both Systems):**
- BankNum (4 digits)
- MerchantNum (2-16 digits)

**Express-Only Data:**
- Legal Name, DBA
- Tax ID
- Business Address
- Owner Information
- MCC
- Processing Limits

**PPM-Only Data:**
- Fee Items
- Pricing Rates
- ERG Assignments
- Agent Assignments (for RP)
- Minimum Discount
- Rate Restrictions

**Shared/Referenced:**
- DDA Account Numbers (Express creates, PPM references)
- Bank routing numbers
- Merchant status

**5. Error Handling:**

If PPM receives a request for non-existent merchant:
```xml
<Response>
  <ResponseMetaData>
    <Code>ERROR_CODE</Code>
    <Description>Merchant not found in billing system</Description>
  </ResponseMetaData>
</Response>
```

Resolution: Ensure merchant exists in Express and is boarded before calling PPM.

### B. Data Validation Strategy

**1. Pre-submission Validation:**
```typescript
interface ValidationRule {
  field: string;
  validate: (value: any) => boolean;
  message: string;
}

const merchantPricingRules: ValidationRule[] = [
  {
    field: 'merchant.bankNum',
    validate: (v) => /^\d{4}$/.test(v),
    message: 'Bank number must be 4 digits'
  },
  {
    field: 'merchant.merchantNum',
    validate: (v) => /^\d{2,16}$/.test(v),
    message: 'Merchant number must be 2-16 digits'
  },
  // ... more rules
];

function validatePPMRequest(request: any): ValidationResult {
  const errors: string[] = [];
  
  for (const rule of merchantPricingRules) {
    const value = getNestedValue(request, rule.field);
    if (!rule.validate(value)) {
      errors.push(rule.message);
    }
  }
  
  return { valid: errors.length === 0, errors };
}
```

**2. Key Structure Validation:**
```typescript
// Load valid key structures on startup
const keyStructureCache = new Map<number, Set<string>>();

async function loadKeyStructures() {
  // Fetch from PPM Key Structure File or cached version
  const structures = await fetchPPMKeyStructures();
  
  for (const [category, keys] of structures) {
    keyStructureCache.set(
      category,
      new Set(keys.map(k => k.join('|')))
    );
  }
}

function validateKeyStructure(
  category: number,
  keys: string[]
): boolean {
  const validKeys = keyStructureCache.get(category);
  if (!validKeys) return false;
  
  return validKeys.has(keys.join('|'));
}
```

```typescript
async function loggedPPMOperation<T>(

  const log: PPMOperationLog = {

    bankNum: request.merchant?.bankNum,
    merchantNum: request.merchant?.merchantNum,
    requestSize: JSON.stringify(request).length,
    responseCode: 0,
    responseTime: 0
  };
  
  try {
    const result = await execute();
    log.responseCode = result.responseMetaData?.code || 0;
    log.responseTime = Date.now() - startTime;
    
    // Log to database/monitoring system
    await saveOperationLog(log);
    
    return result;
  } catch (error) {
    log.responseCode = -1;
    log.responseTime = Date.now() - startTime;
    log.errors = [error.message];
    
    await saveOperationLog(log);
    throw error;
  }
}
```

**2. Health Checks:**

```typescript
function validatePPMConfig() {
  const required = [
    'wsdlUrl',
    'clientId',
    'userId',
    'password'
  ];
  
  for (const field of required) {
    if (!ppmConfig[field]) {
      throw new Error(`PPM configuration missing: ${field}`);
    }
  }
}
```

---

## Summary of Critical Integration Points

### 1. **Prerequisites**
- Merchant must exist in TSYS Express
- Merchant must be boarded (status = "B")
- BankNum and MerchantNum must be obtained from Express

### 2. **Primary Operations**
- **SaveMerchantPricing** - Initial pricing setup after Express boarding
- **AddMerchantFees** - Incremental fee additions
- **ModifyMerchantFees** - Rate updates (careful with date matching)
- **GetMerchantPricing** - Validation and retrieval
- **SaveMerchantDDA** - Bank account configuration

### 3. **Data Transformation Requirements**
- MPA discount rates  PPM Discount fees (Category 12)
- MPA monthly fees  PPM MISC Fixed fees (Category 9)
- MPA transaction fees  PPM Auth/Data Capture fees (Categories 1, 3)
- MPA bank account  PPM DDA configuration

### 4. **Critical Business Rules**
- Fee items limited to 80 direct + 80 per hierarchy level
- Key structures must be in valid combinations
- Date ranges: StartDate cannot be in past for new fees
- Effective rates require StopDate on all but final rate
- XML-submitted fees always saved as Complete status

### 5. **Error Handling**
- Check ResponseMetaData.Code (0 = success)
- Check ProfileStatus.Code for profile-level errors
- Check individual Fee.Outcome.Code for fee-level errors
- Log all failed operations for audit trail

content.text:
I've completed a comprehensive review of the TSYS documentation and created a detailed integration implementation plan at `docs/TSYS_Integration_Implementation_Plan.md`.

## Key Findings

**Express API (Account Creation):**
- 30+ commands for full merchant lifecycle management
- Uses `AddPPMMerchant` command (recommended) to create accounts in both Express and PPM simultaneously
- Real-time (HTTPS) and Batch processing modes available
- Returns BankNum + MerchantNum identifiers needed for PPM

**PPM API (Pricing Configuration):**
- SOAP/XML-based API with real-time and batch operations
- 15 fee categories covering discounts, authorizations, monthly fees, transactions
- Supports complex pricing: tiered rates, interchange pass-through, scheduled rate changes
- Must have Express merchant boarded (status = "B") before pricing configuration

## Critical Integration Flow

```
MPA Form  Express (AddPPMMerchant)  Wait for Boarding  PPM (SaveMerchantPricing)  PPM (SaveMerchantDDA)  Validation
```

## What's in the Plan

1. **Complete Architecture** - System overview, tech stack, integration patterns
2. **Phase 1: Express Implementation** - Client setup, AddPPMMerchant operation, data transformers
3. **Phase 2: PPM Implementation** - SOAP client, SaveMerchantPricing, fee transformers
4. **Data Mapping Tables** - MPA fields  Express fields  PPM fees (detailed mappings)
5. **7-Week Implementation Roadmap** - Sprint-by-sprint breakdown
6. **Code Examples** - TypeScript implementations for all key operations
7. **Error Handling** - Retry strategies, recovery workflows, error classifications
8. **Testing Strategy** - Unit, integration, and E2E test specifications
9. **Security & Compliance** - PCI DSS and SOX requirements
10. **Monitoring & Operations** - Metrics, alerting, logging strategies

The plan includes ready-to-use code for Express XML client, PPM SOAP client, data transformers, and the complete orchestration service.
